===Verb===
{{en-verb|bends|bending|bent}}

# {{transitive}} To cause (something) to change its shape into a {{l|en|curve}}, by {{l|en|physical}} {{l|en|force}}, {{l|en|chemical}} action, or any other means. <!--accomplishment,achievement-->
#: ''If you '''bend''' the pipe too far, it will break.''
#: ''Don’t '''bend''' your knees.''
# {{intransitive}}  To become {{l|en|curve|curved}}. <!--activity,accomplishment-->
#: ''Look at the trees '''bending''' in the wind.''
# {{transitive}} To cause to change direction.
# {{intransitive}} To change direction. <!--state,activity-->
#: ''The road '''bends''' to the right''
# {{intransitive|usually|with "down"}} To {{l|en|stoop}}.
#: ''He '''bent''' down to pick up the pieces.''
# {{transitive}} To force to submit. <!--accomplishment,achievement-->
#: ''They '''bent''' me to their will.''
# {{intransitive}} To submit.<!--state?,activity-->
#: ''I am '''bending''' to my desire to eat junk food.''
# {{transitive}} To apply to a task or purpose.<!--state?,activity-->
#: ''He '''bent''' company's resources to gaining market share.''
# {{intransitive}} To apply oneself to a task or purpose.<!--state?,activity-->
#: ''He '''bent''' to the goal of gaining market share.''
# {{transitive}} To adapt or interpret to for a purpose or beneficiary.<!--accomplishment-->
# {{transitive|nautical}} To {{l|en|tie}}, as in {{l|en|securing}} a line to a {{l|en|cleat}}; to {{l|en|shackle}} a {{l|en|chain}} to an {{l|en|anchor}}; make {{l|en|fast}}.<!--accomplishment,achievement-->
#: '''''Bend''' the sail to the yard.''
# {{transitive|music}} To smoothly change the pitch of a note.<!--activity,accomplishment-->
#: ''You should '''bend''' the G slightly sharp in the next measure.''
# {{intransitive|nautical}} To {{l|en|swing}} the {{l|en|body}} when {{l|en|rowing}}.<!--activity-->

